HEADWORD: Daysman
<hw>Days"man</hw> <pr>(d⟦amac⟧z"m⟦acr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>day</ets> in the sense of <it>day fixed for trial</it>.]</ety>
<def>An umpire or arbiter; a mediator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither is there any <qex>daysman</qex> betwixt us.</q>
<rj><qau>Job ix. 33.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dayspring</ent>⟦br⟧
